arch results, here's what I found regarding Novo Nordisk's leadership and related information:\n\n## CEO Transition\n\nMaziar Mike Doustdar was appointed as president and chief executive officer effective August 7, 2025, succeeding Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen, who stepped down on the same date. Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen was the chief executive of Novo Nordisk between January 2017 and August 2025.\n\n## New CEO Background\n\nMike Doustdar, currently Novo Nordisk's executive vice president of International Operations, has a strong track record of creating value and driving growth, with Novo Nordisk's International Operations more than doubling sales to approximately DKK 112 billion in 2024 under his leadership over the past decade.\n\n## Management Ownership\n\nNovo Nordisk's CEO Maziar Doustdar, appointed in August 2025, directly owns 0.002% of the company's shares, worth DKK20.10M.\n\n## Other Executive Changes\n\nEmil Kongshøj Larsen, currently senior vice president of the Europe and Canada region (EUCAN), will join Executive Management and succeed Mike Doustdar, assuming the responsibility of executive vice president, International Operations. Novo Nordisk decided to merge Research & Early Development with its Development area into a new, consolidated R&D unit under the leadership of Martin Holst Lange, who was appointed chief scientific officer effective August 7.\n\nThe search results do not contain specific information about compensation details or the 2025 proxy statement for the management team."],"durationSeconds":14.690618292}}
