rdisk expects its sales to decline, on an adjusted basis, by between 5% and 13% this year.\n\nBack then, a U.S. insulin price war dragged down results. In contrast, the Danish drugmaker faces multiple headwinds this time around. Pricing pressure in the U.S. market is squeezing margins. Patents for blockbuster drugs Wegovy and Ozempic are expiring in China, Brazil, and Canada.\n\n## Key Factors Behind the Decline\n\nThey agreed to cut prices for their best-selling drugs for Medicare and Medicaid patients. But they'll ultimately hurt total sales numbers. Additionally, competition from Eli Lilly and compounders further constricted market share.\n\n## Market Reaction\n\nThe guidance announcement triggered a sharp stock market reaction. Shares crashed up to 14% in afternoon trading after a brief halt."],"durationSeconds":5.549840375}}
