tes is the largest institutional shareholder, holding 0.42% of NVO shares.\n\nIt's worth noting that the ownership percentages vary slightly depending on the data source and timing, but the overall picture shows that while Novo Holdings/Novo Nordisk Foundation maintains significant voting control through the A shares, institutional ownership of the publicly traded shares remains relatively limited."],"durationSeconds":4.899144707999993}}
