Nordisk's CEO, management team, and related information. Here are the key findings:\n\n## CEO Leadership Change\n\nMaziar Mike Doustdar was appointed as president and chief executive officer of Novo Nordisk, effective August 7, 2025. He succeeded Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen, who stepped down as president and chief executive officer on the same date.\n\n## Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen's Tenure\n\nLars Fruergaard Jørgensen was the chief executive of Novo Nordisk between January 2017 and August 2025. He had 34 years of commitment to the company.\n\n## New CEO and Management Structure\n\nMike Doustdar, as Novo Nordisk's executive vice president of International Operations, has driven growth with International Operations more than doubling sales to approximately DKK 112 billion in 2024.\n\nEmil Kongshøj Larsen, currently senior vice president of the Europe and Canada region (EUCAN), joined Executive Management and assumed the responsibility of executive vice president, International Operations.\n\nNovo Nordisk merged its Research & Early Development with its Development area into a new consolidated R&D unit, with Martin Holst Lange, MD, PhD, appointed as chief scientific officer, effective August 7.\n\n## Ownership Information\n\nNovo Nordisk's CEO Maziar Doustdar, appointed in August 2025, directly owns 0.002% of the company's shares, worth $4.67M.\n\nThe search results did not contain specific information about CFO details or proxy compensation statements for 2025.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"63953807-54da-4e4a-a0f9-cb4a0b97eca8","uuid":"d2b84d92-f156-42bb-b387-ad02f251e8e5","timestamp":"2026-04-28T17:05:09.992Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"Novo Nordisk CEO Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen management team CFO proxy compensation ownership 2025","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01TFfEt8Q17oFxm3E1eCQVxX","content":[{"title":"Company announcement","url":"https:/