{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NkvxVNHYELuJE2MtfDxQ2k","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Novo Nordisk NVO competitive moat patents GLP-1 competition Eli Lilly tirzepatide market share 2025 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Eli Lilly gaining in GLP-1 market over Novo Nordisk, earnings show\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/04/eli-lilly-novo-nordisk-earnings-glp1-market.html\"},{\"title\":\"Who's Winning the Intense Battle to Rule the White-Hot GLP-1 Drug Market? | The Motley Fool\",\"url\":\"https://www.fool.com/investing/2025/11/11/win-intense-battle-rule-glp-1-drug-lly-nvo-pfe/\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk's Strategic Reset: From GLP-1 Monopoly to Focused Obesity Arms Race (NYSE:NVO) - NVO Analysis - BeyondSPX\",\"url\":\"https://beyondspx.com/quote/NVO/novo-nordisk-s-strategic-reset-from-glp-1-monopoly-to-focused-obesity-arms-race-nyse-nvo\"},{\"title\":\"Can anything threaten Novo and Lilly’s obesity market dominance? | PharmaVoice\",\"url\":\"https://www.pharmavoice.com/news/novo-nordisk-eli-lilly-obesity-market-dominance-glp1/745823/\"},{\"title\":\"3 ways the GLP-1 market has changed shape this year | PharmaVoice\",\"url\":\"https://www.pharmavoice.com/news/glp-1-market-changes-eli-lilly-novo-nordisk-earnings/757312/\"},{\"title\":\"I Expect Novo Nordisk To Outperform Eli Lilly In 2026: Here's Why | Seeking Alpha\",\"url\":\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4857159-i-expect-novo-nordisk-to-outperform-eli-lilly-in-2026-heres-why\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk Isn't A Quality Company - by Jacob B\",\"url\":\"https://thejnicholas.substack.com/p/novo-nordisk-isnt-a-quality-company\"},{\"title\":\"Cross-Sector Collaboration Between Pharma and AI. Novo Nordisk Joins Forces With OpenAI, Can It Regain Market Dominance in the Competition With Eli Lilly?\",\"url\":\"https://www.tradingkey.com/analysis/stocks/us-stocks/261783938-novo-nordisk-openai-pharma-lilly-weight-loss-drug-discovery-market-share-glp1-tradingkey\"},{\"title\":\"What is Competitive Landscape of Novo Nordisk Company? – MatrixBCG.com\",\"url\":\"https://matrixbcg.com/blogs/competitors/novonordisk\"},{\"title\":\"Eli Lilly vs Novo Nordisk: Which Company Will Dominate the Weight Loss Drug Market in 2026? | The Motley Fool\",\"url\":\"https://www.fool.com/investing/2026/01/13/eli-lilly-vs-novo-nordisk-which-to-dominate-2026/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's a comprehensive overview of the competitive dynamics between Novo Nordisk and Eli Lilly in the GLP-1 market:\n\n## Market Share Dynamics\n\nEli Lilly currently holds approximately 60% market share in the U.S. GLP-1 market, with Novo Nordisk losing its leadership position in the fastest-growing and most profitable weight-loss drug segment. In 2025, tirzepatide generated approximately $36.5 billion in revenue, with semaglutide following closely at $36.1 billion.\n\nNovo Nordisk's market share in international operations has eroded from 80% to 50% amid Eli Lilly's competitive onslaught. Novo's U.S. Wegovy weekly prescriptions have plateaued around 270,000 units, while Lilly's tirzepatide prescriptions grew 8% in the same period Novo's semaglutide grew just 2%.\n\n## Clinical and Product Advantages\n\nTirzepatide is considered \"superior\" in effectiveness and tolerability compared to semaglutide, as proven in a head-to-head clinical trial conducted by Lilly in 2024, with prescription trends showing that the company's drugs are preferred among prescribers. In clinical trials, tirzepatide performed 30-40% more effective than semaglutide for weight loss, plus giving less nausea.\n\n## Patent Protection & Competitive Moat\n\nLilly's tirzepatide should be protected into \"the back half of the 2030s\" in major markets. In contrast, Novo has filed 320 patent applications for its three semaglutide drugs and has been granted 154, with its main patent for semaglutide set to expire at the end of 2031. However, Novo has also been granted another 49 patents that cover minor modifications to the products and offer exclusivity protections through 2042.\n\n## 2026 Outlook\n\nThis year will see how Lilly's upcoming obesity pill, orforglipron, fares against Novo's own oral Wegovy drug, which has had an explosive U.S. launch this year. In December 2025, Novo Nordisk's oral weight-loss version of semaglutide was approved and launched in January 2026, while on April 1, Eli Lilly's oral small-molecule GLP-1 drug Orforglipron received FDA approval.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"63953807-54da-4e4a-a0f9-cb4a0b97eca8","uuid":"7010a3a9-6927-40b5-b491-fceee84e2c22","timestamp":"2026-04-28T17:05:27.578Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"Novo Nordisk NVO competitive moat patents GLP-1 competition Eli Lilly tirzepatide market share 2025 2026","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01NDP1u9juCbEH4r3G7zELGP","content":[{"title":"Eli Lilly gaining in GLP-1 market over Novo Nordisk, earnings show","url":"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/04/eli-lilly-novo-nordisk-earnings-glp1-market.html"},{"title":"Who's Winning the Intense Battle to Rule the White-Hot GLP-1 Drug Market? | The Motley Fool","url":"https://www.fool.com/investing/2025/11/11/win-intense-battle-rule-glp-1-drug-lly-nvo-pfe/"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk's Strategic Reset: From GLP-1 Monopoly to Focused Obesity Arms Race (NYSE:NVO) - NVO Analysis - BeyondSPX","url":"https://beyondspx.com/quote/NVO/novo-nordisk-s-strategic-reset-from-glp-1-monopoly-to-focused-obesity-arms-race-nyse-nvo"},{"title":"Can anything threaten Novo and Lilly’s obesity market dominance? | PharmaVoice","url":"https://www.pharmavoice.com/news/novo-nordisk-eli-lilly-obesity-market-dominance-glp1/745823/"},{"title":"3 ways the GLP-1 market has changed shape this year | PharmaVoice","url":"https://www.pharmavoice.com/news/glp-1-market-changes-eli-lilly-novo-nordisk-earnings/757312/"},{"title":"I Expect Novo Nordisk To Outperform Eli Lilly In 2026: Here's Why | Seeking Alpha","url":"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4857159-i-expect-novo-nordisk-to-outperform-eli-lilly-in-2026-heres-why"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk Isn't A Quality Company - by Jacob B","url":"https://thejnicholas.substack.com/p/novo-nordisk-isnt-a-quality-company"},{"title":"Cross-Sector Collaboration Between Pharma and AI. Novo Nordisk Joins Forces With OpenAI, Can It Regain Market Dominance in the Competition With Eli Lilly?","url":"https://www.tradingkey.com/analysis/stocks/us-stocks/261783938-novo-nordisk-openai-pharma-lilly-weight-loss-drug-discovery-market-share-glp1-tradingkey"},{"title":"What is Competitive Landscape of Novo Nordisk Company? – MatrixBCG.com","url":"https://matrixbcg.com/blogs/competitors/novonordisk"},{"title":"Eli Lilly vs Novo Nordisk: Which Company Will Dominate the Weight Loss Drug Market in 2026? | The Motley Fool","url":"https://www.fool.com/investing/2026/01/13/eli-lilly-vs-novo-nordisk-which-to-dominate-2026/"}]},"Based on the search results, here's a comprehensive overview of the competitive dynamics between Novo Nordisk and Eli Lilly in the GLP-1 market:\n\n## Market Share Dynamics\n\nEli Lilly currently holds approximately 60% market share in the U.S. GLP-1 market, with Novo Nordisk losing its leadership position in the fastest-growing and most profitable weight-loss drug segment. In 2025, tirzepatide generated approximately $36.5 billion in revenue, with semaglutide following closely at $36.1 billion.\n\nNovo Nordisk's market share in international operations has eroded from 80% to 50% amid Eli Lilly's competitive onslaught. Novo's U.S. Wegovy weekly prescriptions have plateaued around 270,000 units, while Lilly's tirzepatide prescriptions grew 8% in the same period Novo's semaglutide grew just 2%.\n\n## Clinical and Product Advantages\n\nTirzepatide is considered \"superior\" in effectiveness and tolerability compared to semaglutide, as proven in a head-to-head clinical trial conducted by Lilly in 2024, with prescription trends showing that the company's drugs are preferred among prescribers. In clinical trials, tirzepatide performed 30-40% more effective than semaglutide for weight loss, plus giving less nausea.\n\n## Patent Protection & Competitive Moat\n\nLilly's tirzepatide should be protected into \"the back half of the 2030s\" in major markets. In contrast, Novo has filed 320 patent applications for its three semaglutide drugs and has been granted 154, with its main patent for semaglutide set to expire at the end of 2031. However, Novo has also been granted another 49 patents that cover minor modifications to the products and offer exclusivity protections through 2042.\n\n## 2026 Outlook\n\nThis year will see how Lilly's upcoming obesity pill, orforglipron, fares against Novo's own oral Wegovy drug, which has had an explosive U.S. launch this year. In December 2025, Novo Nordisk's oral weight-loss version of semaglutide was approved and launched in January 2026, while on April 1, Eli Lilly's oral small-molecule GLP-1 drug Orforglipron received FDA approval."],"durationSeconds":10.957247875000009}}
