{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XAjDqEzUJVjyQyrXi9D21N","type":"tool_result","content":"# Novo Nordisk (NVO) Annual Cash Flow Data 2021-2025\n\n| Metric | FY 2025 | FY 2024 | FY 2023 | FY 2022 | FY 2021 |\n|--------|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|\n| Operating Cash Flow | 119,102 | 120,968 | 108,908 | 78,887 | 55,000 |\n| Capital Expenditures | (60,140) | (47,164) | (25,806) | (12,146) | (6,335) |\n| Free Cash Flow | 58,962 | 73,804 | 83,102 | 66,741 | 48,665 |\n| Dividends Paid | (51,763) | (44,140) | (31,767) | (25,303) | (21,517) |\n| Share Repurchases | (1,388) | (20,181) | (29,924) | (24,086) | (19,447) |\n\n**Key Observations:**\n\nOperating cash flow remained relatively stable around 120 billion DKK in 2024-2025 after growing significantly from 2021-2023. Capital expenditures increased substantially, rising from 6.3 billion to 60.1 billion DKK, reflecting \"Purchases of Intangible Assets\" of 30 billion DKK in 2025. Consequently, free cash flow declined 20% year-over-year. Dividend payments and share repurchases trended upward overall, demonstrating consistent shareholder returns despite lower cash generation."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"63953807-54da-4e4a-a0f9-cb4a0b97eca8","uuid":"1112b1c0-dc31-42d5-a8ea-fb9f6e0632a1","timestamp":"2026-04-28T17:06:02.039Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":115508,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Novo Nordisk (NVO) Annual Cash Flow Data 2021-2025\n\n| Metric | FY 2025 | FY 2024 | FY 2023 | FY 2022 | FY 2021 |\n|--------|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|\n| Operating Cash Flow | 119,102 | 120,968 | 108,908 | 78,887 | 55,000 |\n| Capital Expenditures | (60,140) | (47,164) | (25,806) | (12,146) | (6,335) |\n| Free Cash Flow | 58,962 | 73,804 | 83,102 | 66,741 | 48,665 |\n| Dividends Paid | (51,763) | (44,140) | (31,767) | (25,303) | (21,517) |\n| Share Repurchases | (1,388) | (20,181) | (29,924) | (24,086) | (19,447) |\n\n**Key Observations:**\n\nOperating cash flow remained relatively stable around 120 billion DKK in 2024-2025 after growing significantly from 2021-2023. Capital expenditures increased substantially, rising from 6.3 billion to 60.1 billion DKK, reflecting \"Purchases of Intangible Assets\" of 30 billion DKK in 2025. Consequently, free cash flow declined 20% year-over-year. Dividend payments and share repurchases trended upward overall, demonstrating consistent shareholder returns despite lower cash generation.","durationMs":4088,"url":"https://stockanalysis.com/stocks/nvo/financials/cash-flow-statement/"}}
