ictions including Brazil, Canada and China will \"probably lead to a decreasing top line\". In 2026-2027, revenue loss is expected to be more pronounced, with localized patent expirations in key emerging markets such as China, Brazil, India, and Canada projected to result in a 5-8% share loss.\n\n## GLP-1 Competition\n\nCompetition is likely to intensify beyond Lilly and compounders, as several drugmakers — including Pfizer, Amgen, AstraZeneca, Roche — advance late-stage candidates through their pipelines. Eli Lilly's Tirzepatide (Mounjaro) has emerged as a formidable competitor, surpassing Wegovy in several regions due to strategic collaborations.\n\n## Oral Semaglutide Progress\n\nOral Wegovy successfully launched in 2025, offering a needle-free option for patients, though oral Wegovy outsells Lilly's pill 5-to-1.\n\n## Pipeline Challenges\n\nCagriSema, the next-generation dual-agonist, had a Phase 3 trial in February 2026 that failed to show superiority over Lilly's tirzepatide.\n\n## Overall Financial Outlook\n\nManagement has guided for a 5% to 13% decline in both adjusted revenue and profit for 2026, driven by U.S. pricing pressure and patent expirations in select markets."],"durationSeconds":10.597271458000003}}
