ml"}]},"Based on the web search results, here is a comprehensive breakdown of Novo Nordisk's segment revenue for GLP-1 products:\n\n## 2024 Annual Results\n\n**Obesity Care (Wegovy & Saxenda):**\nSales of obesity care products increased by 56-57% at constant exchange rates to DKK 65,146 million. More specifically, Wegovy sales for all of 2024 totaled 58.2 billion kroner (around $8 billion), compared to 31.3 billion kroner the prior year.\n\n**Diabetes Care (GLP-1 Products):**\nSales in Diabetes care increased by 19-20% at constant exchange rates to DKK 206,618 million driven by growth of GLP-1-based products and insulins. Within this segment, GLP-1-based products for type 2 diabetes (Rybelsus, Ozempic and Victoza) increased by 21-22% at constant exchange rates to DKK 149,125 million.\n\n**Ozempic Specifically:**\nOzempic sales increased by 26% to DKK 120,342 million, with Ozempic bringing home around 120 billion kroner (nearly $17 billion) over the same stretch.\n\n## 2025 Full Year Results\n\nWegovy sales reached DKK 79,106 million and Ozempic DKK 127,089 million in 2025, with obesity products Saxenda and Wegovy generating DKK 82,347 million in total.\n\nGLP-1-based products for type 2 diabetes increased by 2-6% at constant exchange rates to DKK 152,202 million."],"durationSeconds":7.049636749999998}}
