ighest target at $160 by Cantor Fitzgerald and the lowest at $41 from Goldman Sachs.\n- According to projections from 12 analysts, the average 12-month price target for Novo Nordisk ADR is 46.63 USD, with a high estimate of 65.83 USD and a low estimate of 36.05 USD.\n- TipRanks shows a consensus rating of Hold with an average price target for Novo Nordisk of 43.00.\n\nThe wide variance in price targets reflects mixed sentiment among analysts regarding the company's growth prospects and risks."],"durationSeconds":7.003919499999997}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Xo4noREsuPpffRcgjc1mJV","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Novo Nordisk CEO CFO management team Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen proxy compensation ownership 2025\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Company announcement\",\"url\":\"https://www.novonordisk.com/content/nncorp/global/en/news-and-media/news-and-ir-materials/news-details.html?id=916408\"},{\"title\":\"Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lars_Fruergaard_J%C3%B8rgensen\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk Names New CEO; Makes Other Leadership Changes - DCAT Value Chain Insights\",\"url\":\"https://www.dcatvci.org/top-industry-news/novo-nordisk-names-new-ceo-makes-other-leadership-changes/\"},{\"title\":\"Meet Novo Nordisk's Executive Management team\",\"url\":\"https://www.novonordisk.com/about/executive-management.html\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk A/S (NOVO B) Leadership & Management Team Analysis - Simply Wall St\",\"url\":\"https://simplywall.st/stocks/dk/pharmaceuticals-biotech/cph-novo-b/novo-nordisk-shares/management\"},{\"title\":\"Will New CEO's Leadership Propel Novo Nordisk's Next Growth Wave?\",\"url\":\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/ceos-leadership-propel-novo-nordisks-130600201.html\"},{\"title\":\"Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen\",\"url\":\"https://www.novonordisk.com/about/executive-management/lars-fruergaard-jorgensen.html\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk’s New CEO and Denmark’s Economic Shift\",\"url\":\"https://www.ceotodaymagazine.com/2025/11/novo-nordisk-denmark-economic-shift/\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk A/S (NVO) Leadership & Management Team Analysis - Simply Wall St\",\"url\":\"https://simplywall.st/stocks/us/pharmaceuticals-biotech/nyse-nvo/novo-nordisk/management\"},{\"title\":\"Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen | ISPE | International Society for Pharmaceutical Engineering\",\"url\":\"https://ispe.org/people/lars-fruergaard-jorgensen\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found regarding Novo Nordisk's management team and leadership:\n\n## CEO Leadership Change\n\nMaziar Mike Doustdar was appointed as president and chief executive officer of Novo Nordisk, effective August 7, 2025, succeeding Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen, who stepped down on the same date.\n\n## Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen's Tenure\n\nLars Fruergaard Jørgensen was the chief executive of Novo Nordisk between January 2017 and August 2025. He joined Novo Nordisk in 1991 as an economist and served over 34 years with the company in roles across Europe, USA and Japan with increasing responsibilities.\n\n## New CEO Background\n\nMike Doustdar, currently Novo Nordisk's executive vice president of International Operations, has a strong track record of creating value, and under his leadership over the past decade, Novo Nordisk's International Operations have more than doubled sales to approximately DKK 112 billion in 2024.\n\n## Executive Management Changes\n\nMartin Holst Lange, currently executive vice president, Development, will be appointed chief scientific officer (CSO), effective August 7, and the company's Research & Early Development and Development areas will be merged into a new, consolidated R&D unit. Emil Kongshøj Larsen, currently senior vice president of the Europe and Canada region (EUCAN), will join Executive Management and succeed Mike Doustdar as executive vice president, International Operations.\n\n## Ownership Information\n\nNovo Nordisk's CEO Maziar Doustdar, appointed in August 2025, directly owns 0.002% of the company's shares, worth DKK20.10M.\n\nThe search results did not contain specific information about a CFO or detailed proxy compensation details for 2025.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c2f9e2bf-4eb3-44bc-922b-8db97158fefa","uuid":"c0e04bef-8f3c-4623-91c1-3d59360f86b4","timestamp":"2026-04-28T22:24:32.206Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"Novo Nordisk CEO CFO management team Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen proxy compensation ownership 2025","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_018fLfsVUMcqiZY4PoicJ24d","content":[{"title":"Company announcement","url":"https://www.novonordisk.com/content/nncorp/global/en/news-and-media/news-and-ir-materials/news-details.html?id=916408"},{"title":"Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen - Wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lars_Fruergaard_J%C3%B8rgensen"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk Names New CEO; Makes Other Leadership Changes - DCAT Value Chain Insights","url":"https://www.dcatvci.org/top-industry-news/novo-nordisk-names-new-ceo-makes-other-leadership-changes/"},{"title":"Meet Novo Nordisk's Executive Management team","url":"https://www.novonordisk.com/about/executive-management.html"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk A/S (NOVO B) Leadership & Management Team Analysis - Simply Wall St","url":"https://simplywall.st/stocks/dk/pharmaceuticals-biotech/cph-novo-b/novo-nordisk-shares/management"},{"title":"Will New CEO's Leadership Propel Novo Nordisk's Next Growth Wave?","url":"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/ceos-leadership-propel-novo-nordisks-130600201.html"},{"title":"Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen","url":"https://www.novonordisk.com/about/executive-management/lars-fruergaard-jorgensen.html"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk’s New CEO and Denmark’s Economic Shift","url":"https://www.ceotodaymagazine.com/2025/11/novo-nordisk-denmark-economic-shift/"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk A/S (NVO) Leadership & Management Team Analysis - Simply Wall St","url":"https://simplywall.st/stocks/us/pharmaceuticals-biotech/nyse-nvo/novo-nordisk/management"},{"title":"Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen | ISPE | International Society for Pharmaceutical Engineering","url":"https://ispe.org/people/lars-fruergaard-jorgensen"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found regarding Novo Nordisk's management team and leadership:\n\n## CEO Leadership Change\n\nMaziar Mike Doustdar was appointed as president and chief executive officer of Novo Nordisk, effective August 7, 2025, succeeding Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen, who stepped down on the same date.\n\n## Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen's Tenure\n\nLars Fruergaard Jørgensen was the chief executive of Novo Nordisk between January 2017 and August 2025. He joined Novo Nordisk in 1991 as an economist and served over 34 years with the company in roles across Europe, USA and Japan with increasing responsibilities.\n\n## New CEO Background\n\nMike Doustdar, currently Novo Nordisk's executive vice president of International Operations, has a strong track record of creating value, and under his leadership over the past decade, Novo Nordisk's International Operations have more than doubled sales to approximately DKK 112 billion in 2024.\n\n## Executive Management Changes\n\nMartin Holst Lange, currently executive vice president, Development, will be appointed chief scientific officer (CSO), effective August 7, and the company's Research & Early Development and Development areas will be merged into a new, consolidated R&D unit. Emil Kongshøj Larsen, currently senior vice president of the Europe and Canada region (EUCAN), will join Executive Management and succeed Mike Doustdar as executive vice president, International Operations.\n\n## Ownership Information\n\nNovo Nordisk's CEO Maziar Doustdar, appointed in August 2025, directly owns 0.002% of the company's shares, worth DKK20.10M.\n\nThe search results did not contain specific information about a CFO or detailed proxy compensation details for 2025."],"durationSeconds":7.7357178339999955}}
