{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LeGFK3K9GtvV7yW9kusuyi","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Novo Nordisk competitors Eli Lilly GILD LLY Sanofi AstraZeneca valuation EV EBITDA PE comparison 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"I Expect Novo Nordisk To Outperform Eli Lilly In 2026: Here's Why | Seeking Alpha\",\"url\":\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4857159-i-expect-novo-nordisk-to-outperform-eli-lilly-in-2026-heres-why\"},{\"title\":\"Largest Pharmaceutical Companies by Market Cap in 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.alpha-sense.com/largest-pharmaceutical-companies-by-market-cap/\"},{\"title\":\"Eli Lilly Vs. Novo Nordisk: The Valuation Gap Is Unreasonable (NYSE:NVO) | Seeking Alpha\",\"url\":\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4876511-eli-lilly-vs-novo-nordisk-the-valuation-gap-is-unreasonable\"},{\"title\":\"These 4 charts show the scale of Novo Nordisk's woes\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/25/novo-nordisk-stock-nvo-lly-eli-lilly-ozempic-weight-loss-obesity.html\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk vs. Eli Lilly: What's the Better Long-Term Investment? | The Motley Fool\",\"url\":\"https://www.fool.com/investing/2026/02/09/novo-nordisk-vs-eli-lilly-whats-the-better-long-te/\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk Vs. Eli Lilly: Cheap Vs. Expensive, But No Clear Opportunity (NYSE:NVO) | Seeking Alpha\",\"url\":\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4885662-novo-nordisk-eli-lilly-cheap-vs-expensive-but-no-clear-opportunity\"},{\"title\":\"As Lilly flourishes in Q4, peer projections signal looming sector slowdown in 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.fiercepharma.com/pharma/while-lilly-continues-boom-q4-many-other-drugmakers-are-projecting-slide-26\"},{\"title\":\"NVO (Novo Nordisk A/S) vs LLY (Eli Lilly and Co) Comparison - Alpha Spread\",\"url\":\"https://www.alphaspread.com/comparison/nyse/nvo/vs/nyse/lly\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk Vs. Eli Lilly: The Tide May Be Turning For The Underdog (NYSE:NVO) | Seeking Alpha\",\"url\":\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4862487-novo-nordisk-v-eli-lilly-the-tide-may-be-turning-for-the-underdog\"},{\"title\":\"Eli Lilly vs Novo Nordisk: Which Company Will Dominate the Weight Loss Drug Market in 2026? | The Motley Fool\",\"url\":\"https://www.fool.com/investing/2026/01/13/eli-lilly-vs-novo-nordisk-which-to-dominate-2026/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found regarding Novo Nordisk and its competitors in 2026:\n\n## Market Position and Competition\n\nThe largest pharmaceutical companies by market cap in 2026 are Eli Lilly, Johnson & Johnson, AbbVie, AstraZeneca, and Merck. Despite being first to launch a GLP-1 drug for weight loss, Novo's market share has eroded, and the company now only captures about 40% of the market, while rival Eli Lilly holds 60%, according to most estimates.\n\n## Valuation Comparison\n\nNovo Nordisk A/S is rated Buy with FDA oral Wegovy, solid fundamentals, and low P/E vs. Eli Lilly. Eli Lilly trades at a vastly higher premium than Novo Nordisk. \n\nHowever, there's debate about the valuation gap. NVO appears cheap due to high dependence on semaglutide and lack of near-term pipeline catalysts, justifying its discounted valuation. LLY is executing very well and is more diversified, but the valuation already reflects much of this.\n\n## Financial Performance in 2026\n\nEarlier this month, Novo Nordisk said it expected sales and profits to drop by between 5% and 13% in 2026. In contrast, Eli Lilly continued its reign with by far the largest revenue growth in the fourth quarter at 43%, which was nearly triple that of second-place Daiichi Sankyo at 15%.\n\nUnfortunately, the search results don't provide specific EV/EBITDA or detailed PE ratio comparisons for all the competitors you mentioned (GILD, Sanofi). Would you like me to search for more specific valuation metrics?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c2f9e2bf-4eb3-44bc-922b-8db97158fefa","uuid":"2a47726e-cdb4-4396-8d76-a84ae49af797","timestamp":"2026-04-28T22:25:07.600Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"Novo Nordisk competitors Eli Lilly GILD LLY Sanofi AstraZeneca valuation EV EBITDA PE comparison 2026","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01A9vPJMgRtPeuUjJ1xjZZPf","content":[{"title":"I Expect Novo Nordisk To Outperform Eli Lilly In 2026: Here's Why | Seeking Alpha","url":"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4857159-i-expect-novo-nordisk-to-outperform-eli-lilly-in-2026-heres-why"},{"title":"Largest Pharmaceutical Companies by Market Cap in 2026","url":"https://www.alpha-sense.com/largest-pharmaceutical-companies-by-market-cap/"},{"title":"Eli Lilly Vs. Novo Nordisk: The Valuation Gap Is Unreasonable (NYSE:NVO) | Seeking Alpha","url":"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4876511-eli-lilly-vs-novo-nordisk-the-valuation-gap-is-unreasonable"},{"title":"These 4 charts show the scale of Novo Nordisk's woes","url":"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/25/novo-nordisk-stock-nvo-lly-eli-lilly-ozempic-weight-loss-obesity.html"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk vs. Eli Lilly: What's the Better Long-Term Investment? | The Motley Fool","url":"https://www.fool.com/investing/2026/02/09/novo-nordisk-vs-eli-lilly-whats-the-better-long-te/"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk Vs. Eli Lilly: Cheap Vs. Expensive, But No Clear Opportunity (NYSE:NVO) | Seeking Alpha","url":"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4885662-novo-nordisk-eli-lilly-cheap-vs-expensive-but-no-clear-opportunity"},{"title":"As Lilly flourishes in Q4, peer projections signal looming sector slowdown in 2026","url":"https://www.fiercepharma.com/pharma/while-lilly-continues-boom-q4-many-other-drugmakers-are-projecting-slide-26"},{"title":"NVO (Novo Nordisk A/S) vs LLY (Eli Lilly and Co) Comparison - Alpha Spread","url":"https://www.alphaspread.com/comparison/nyse/nvo/vs/nyse/lly"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk Vs. Eli Lilly: The Tide May Be Turning For The Underdog (NYSE:NVO) | Seeking Alpha","url":"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4862487-novo-nordisk-v-eli-lilly-the-tide-may-be-turning-for-the-underdog"},{"title":"Eli Lilly vs Novo Nordisk: Which Company Will Dominate the Weight Loss Drug Market in 2026? | The Motley Fool","url":"https://www.fool.com/investing/2026/01/13/eli-lilly-vs-novo-nordisk-which-to-dominate-2026/"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found regarding Novo Nordisk and its competitors in 2026:\n\n## Market Position and Competition\n\nThe largest pharmaceutical companies by market cap in 2026 are Eli Lilly, Johnson & Johnson, AbbVie, AstraZeneca, and Merck. Despite being first to launch a GLP-1 drug for weight loss, Novo's market share has eroded, and the company now only captures about 40% of the market, while rival Eli Lilly holds 60%, according to most estimates.\n\n## Valuation Comparison\n\nNovo Nordisk A/S is rated Buy with FDA oral Wegovy, solid fundamentals, and low P/E vs. Eli Lilly. Eli Lilly trades at a vastly higher premium than Novo Nordisk. \n\nHowever, there's debate about the valuation gap. NVO appears cheap due to high dependence on semaglutide and lack of near-term pipeline catalysts, justifying its discounted valuation. LLY is executing very well and is more diversified, but the valuation already reflects much of this.\n\n## Financial Performance in 2026\n\nEarlier this month, Novo Nordisk said it expected sales and profits to drop by between 5% and 13% in 2026. In contrast, Eli Lilly continued its reign with by far the largest revenue growth in the fourth quarter at 43%, which was nearly triple that of second-place Daiichi Sankyo at 15%.\n\nUnfortunately, the search results don't provide specific EV/EBITDA or detailed PE ratio comparisons for all the competitors you mentioned (GILD, Sanofi). Would you like me to search for more specific valuation metrics?"],"durationSeconds":7.158235958000005}}
