uthority. The search results also reference a Novo Nordisk Remuneration Report for 2025, which was published in February 2026, that may contain additional detailed compensation information."],"durationSeconds":5.953102083000005}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011cMsPJPoACACtxpu6Bac51","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Novo Nordisk NVO risks 2025 2026 GLP-1 patent expiry compounding pharmacy biosimilar competition price pressure\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk: Downgrading To 'Sell' As GLP-1 Pipeline Faces Many Risks (NYSE:NVO) | Seeking Alpha\",\"url\":\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4888549-novo-nordisk-downgrading-to-sell-as-glp-1-pipeline-faces-many-risks\"},{\"title\":\"Semaglutide patent expiry opens door to GLP-1 generics in Canada\",\"url\":\"https://www.labiotech.eu/in-depth/novo-nordisk-semaglutide-patent-expiration-canada/\"},{\"title\":\"The Battle for Billions: Understanding the Ozempic Patent ...\",\"url\":\"https://journals.library.columbia.edu/index.php/stlr/blog/view/653\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk: Is The GLP‑1 Golden Age Already Behind It? (NYSE:NVO) | Seeking Alpha\",\"url\":\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4892731-novo-nordisk-is-the-glp1-golden-age-already-behind-it\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk's Canadian Mistake | Science | AAAS\",\"url\":\"https://www.science.org/content/blog-post/novo-nordisk-s-canadian-mistake\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk Loses Canadian Semaglutide Patent Protection Over Missed $450 Fee, Opening Door to Generics in 2026\",\"url\":\"https://trial.medpath.com/news/a2e6b94521cbcb41/novo-nordisk-loses-canadian-semaglutide-patent-protection-over-missed-450-fee-opening-door-to-generics-in-2026\"},{\"title\":\"March 20 Patent Expiry Set to Trigger Brutal GLP-1 Price War in India—Novo Nordisk’s Pricing Power Under Direct Threat\",\"url\":\"https://www.ainvest.com/news/march-20-patent-expiry-set-trigger-brutal-glp-1-price-war-india-novo-nordisk-pricing-power-direct-threat-2603/\"},{\"title\":\"The Heavy Price of GLP-1 Drugs: How Financialization Drives Pharmaceutical Patent Abuse and Health Inequities for GLP-1 Therapies\",\"url\":\"https://www.i-mak.org/glp-1/\"},{\"title\":\"Semaglutide (Ozempic) Market: Navigating The Patent Cliff And Strategic Implications\",\"url\":\"https://www.grandviewresearch.com/market-trends/semaglutide-market-navigating-patent-cliff-strategic-implications\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk CFO on 'silver bullet' to address GLP ...\",\"url\":\"https://fortune.com/2025/11/06/novo-nordisk-pantent-innovation-market-leader-cfo-exclusive/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's a comprehensive overview of the risks facing Novo Nordisk (NVO) regarding GLP-1 drugs, patent expiration, and competitive pressures in 2025-2026:\n\n## Patent Expiration Timeline\n\nGeneric and biosimilar competitors are expected to enter the Canadian market as early as January 2026 following semaglutide patent expiration. The key patent for semaglutide in India expires on March 20, 2026. Key emerging markets such as China, Brazil, India, and Canada face localized patent expirations projected to result in a 5-8% share loss in 2026-2027.\n\n## Competitive Threats\n\nNovo Nordisk is facing clinical setbacks, intensifying GLP-1 competition, and patent cliffs. Eli Lilly's Zepbound and Mounjaro have gained U.S. market leadership, with Novo Nordisk losing GLP-1 and diabetes market share in key regions. CagriSema failed to achieve non-inferior weight loss versus Eli Lilly's tirzepatide in the pivotal REDEFINE-4 study.\n\n## Pricing Pressure and Sales Impact\n\nOnce generics enter the market, analysts expect prices of Ozempic and Wegovy to drop by as much as 50 to 80% compared to brand-name versions. Generic versions are projected to be priced at a third to a fifth of the cost of the innovator drug, with price drops of 40% to 50% initially expected. NVO faces a -5% to -13% sales growth outlook for 2026, pressured by generic semaglutide entry in some markets and a thin late-stage pipeline.\n\n## Generic/Biosimilar Competition\n\nGeneric manufacturers including Sandoz, Hikma Pharmaceuticals, and Aspen Pharmacare have confirmed semaglutide dossiers ready for launch once data exclusivity expires in January 2026. Indian pharma giants like Zydus, Dr. Reddy's, and Cipla are poised to launch over 50 branded generics.\n\n## Compounding Challenges\n\nNVO faces margin pressure from U.S. pricing interventions and patent expirations, with generics in markets like India and potential threats in China risking further sales erosion. The company's ability to defend market position while facing simultaneous clinical setbacks in new drug candidates adds to the challenging outlook for 2025-2026.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c2f9e2bf-4eb3-44bc-922b-8db97158fefa","uuid":"8c83458f-52f1-4e8e-acad-75051244c1e4","timestamp":"2026-04-28T22:26:37.371Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"Novo Nordisk NVO risks 2025 2026 GLP-1 patent expiry compounding pharmacy biosimilar competition price pressure","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01Ui1nMDbVVik84YJdaFW394","content":[{"title":"Novo Nordisk: Downgrading To 'Sell' As GLP-1 Pipeline Faces Many Risks (NYSE:NVO) | Seeking Alpha","url":"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4888549-novo-nordisk-downgrading-to-sell-as-glp-1-pipeline-faces-many-risks"},{"title":"Semaglutide patent expiry opens door to GLP-1 generics in Canada","url":"https://www.labiotech.eu/in-depth/novo-nordisk-semaglutide-patent-expiration-canada/"},{"title":"The Battle for Billions: Understanding the Ozempic Patent ...","url":"https://journals.library.columbia.edu/index.php/stlr/blog/view/653"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk: Is The GLP‑1 Golden Age Already Behind It? (NYSE:NVO) | Seeking Alpha","url":"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4892731-novo-nordisk-is-the-glp1-golden-age-already-behind-it"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk's Canadian Mistake | Science | AAAS","url":"https://www.science.org/content/blog-post/novo-nordisk-s-canadian-mistake"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk Loses Canadian Semaglutide Patent Protection Over Missed $450 Fee