{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015zqPvz1ojS2RWDozvVaMZ4","type":"tool_result","content":"# Novo Nordisk Financial Metrics Summary\n\n## 2025 Financial Performance\n\n**Total Sales:** DKK 309,064 million (6% growth in DKK, 10% at constant exchange rates)\n\n**Sales by Therapeutic Area:**\n- Obesity care: DKK 82,347 million (26% growth in DKK, 31% at CER)\n- Diabetes care: DKK 207,109 million (flat in DKK, 4% at CER)\n- Rare disease: DKK 19,608 million (5% growth in DKK, 9% at CER)\n\n**Profitability:**\n- Operating profit: DKK 127,658 million (-1% in DKK, +6% at CER)\n- Net profit: DKK 102,434 million (+1% vs. 2024)\n- Diluted EPS: DKK 23.03 (+2% vs. 2024)\n- Gross margin: 81.0% (down from 84.7% in 2024)\n\n**Cash Flow:**\n- Free cash flow: DKK 28.3 billion (vs. negative DKK 14.7 billion in 2024)\n- Capital expenditure: DKK 60.1 billion (primarily for API and fill-finish capacity)\n\n## 2026 Guidance\n\n**Sales & Operating Profit:**\n- \"Adjusted sales growth at CER -5% to -13%\" reflecting \"lower realised prices\" and \"loss of exclusivity for the semaglutide molecule\"\n- Adjusted operating profit growth: -5% to -13% at CER\n\n**Key Modelling Assumptions:**\n- Financial items (net): approximately DKK 2.3 billion gain\n- Effective tax rate: 21-23%\n- Capital expenditure: approximately DKK 55 billion\n- Free cash flow guidance: DKK 35-45 billion"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eafad868-0c85-44e0-a96c-5a256a92aae5","uuid":"12772eb0-d59f-48c5-93fd-def966740bf1","timestamp":"2026-04-28T22:41:47.863Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":386579,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Novo Nordisk Financial Metrics Summary\n\n## 2025 Financial Performance\n\n**Total Sales:** DKK 309,064 million (6% growth in DKK, 10% at constant exchange rates)\n\n**Sales by Therapeutic Area:**\n- Obesity care: DKK 82,347 million (26% growth in DKK, 31% at CER)\n- Diabetes care: DKK 207,109 million (flat in DKK, 4% at CER)\n- Rare disease: DKK 19,608 million (5% growth in DKK, 9% at CER)\n\n**Profitability:**\n- Operating profit: DKK 127,658 million (-1% in DKK, +6% at CER)\n- Net profit: DKK 102,434 million (+1% vs. 2024)\n- Diluted EPS: DKK 23.03 (+2% vs. 2024)\n- Gross margin: 81.0% (down from 84.7% in 2024)\n\n**Cash Flow:**\n- Free cash flow: DKK 28.3 billion (vs. negative DKK 14.7 billion in 2024)\n- Capital expenditure: DKK 60.1 billion (primarily for API and fill-finish capacity)\n\n## 2026 Guidance\n\n**Sales & Operating Profit:**\n- \"Adjusted sales growth at CER -5% to -13%\" reflecting \"lower realised prices\" and \"loss of exclusivity for the semaglutide molecule\"\n- Adjusted operating profit growth: -5% to -13% at CER\n\n**Key Modelling Assumptions:**\n- Financial items (net): approximately DKK 2.3 billion gain\n- Effective tax rate: 21-23%\n- Capital expenditure: approximately DKK 55 billion\n- Free cash flow guidance: DKK 35-45 billion","durationMs":6095,"url":"https://annualreport.novonordisk.com/2025/strategic-aspirations/financial-performance.html"}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UPT5kTqPSL8zEAUjBMYWRG","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Novo Nordisk CEO Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen CFO management team compensation proxy 2025\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Company announcement\",\"url\":\"https://www.novonordisk.com/content/nncorp/global/en/news-and-media/news-and-ir-materials/news-details.html?id=916408\"},{\"title\":\"Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lars_Fruergaard_J%C3%B8rgensen\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk missed its diversity targets last year. Its CEO paid the price | Fortune\",\"url\":\"https://fortune.com/europe/2025/02/05/novo-nordisk-missed-dei-targets-last-year-ceo-paid-financial-price/\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk Executive Compensation 2025 | NVO CEO Salary\",\"url\":\"https://www.panabee.com/news/novo-nordisk-executive-compensation-2025\"},{\"title\":\"Meet Novo Nordisk's Executive Management team\",\"url\":\"https://www.novonordisk.com/about/executive-management.html\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk A/S (NOVO B) Leadership & Management Team Analysis - Simply Wall St\",\"url\":\"https://simplywall.st/stocks/dk/pharmaceuticals-biotech/cph-novo-b/novo-nordisk-shares/management\"},{\"title\":\"Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen\",\"url\":\"https://www.novonordisk.com/about/executive-management/lars-fruergaard-jorgensen.html\"},{\"title\":\"Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen | ISPE | International Society for Pharmaceutical Engineering\",\"url\":\"https://ispe.org/people/lars-fruergaard-jorgensen\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk Names New CEO; Makes Other Leadership Changes - DCAT Value Chain Insights\",\"url\":\"https://www.dcatvci.org/top-industry-news/novo-nordisk-names-new-ceo-makes-other-leadership-changes/\"},{\"title\":\"NVO - Novo Nordisk AS ADR Executives | Morningstar\",\"url\":\"https://www.morningstar.com/stocks/xnys/nvo/executive\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found regarding Novo Nordisk's CEO, CFO, management team, and compensation:\n\n## CEO Leadership Transition\n\nLars Fruergaard Jørgensen was the chief executive of Novo Nordisk between January 2017 and August 2025. Maziar Mike Doustdar has been appointed as president and chief executive officer, effective 7 August 2025.\n\n## CEO Compensation\n\nThe group's CEO, Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen, received a total remuneration package of DKK 57.1 million ($7.97 million) in 2024, of which 42% is not yet finally determined, and 45% is deferred. Upon departure on August 6, 2025, he received total exit payments and salary of DKK 123.6 million, including a DKK 42.9 million severance and DKK 22.0 million non-compete.\n\n## CFO Compensation\n\nNovo Nordisk's CFO, Karsten Munk Knudsen, reached 67% of his max return based on his individual performance.\n\n## Performance-Based Adjustments\n\nPart of the shortfall in Jørgensen's STIP came from a miss in the company's Purpose & Sustainability and Innovation & Therapeutic Focus subset, where the one area where the group fell short was diversity and inclusion.\n\nThe search results provide information from the 2024 and 2025 proxy materials regarding compensation details for executive leadership.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eafad868-0c85-44e0-a96c-5a256a92aae5","uuid":"f6027442-91e9-4b6b-874f-49c7ad6997f9","timestamp":"2026-04-28T22:41:51.993Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"Novo Nordisk CEO Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen CFO management team compensation proxy 2025","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_017HvnEqs4yEHMXYweyX3MFx","content":[{"title":"Company announcement","url":"https://www.novonordisk.com/content/nncorp/global/en/news-and-media/news-and-ir-materials/news-details.html?id=916408"},{"title":"Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen - Wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lars_Fruergaard_J%C3%B8rgensen"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk missed its diversity targets last year. Its CEO paid the price | Fortune","url":"https://fortune.com/europe/2025/02/05/novo-nordisk-missed-dei-targets-last-year-ceo-paid-financial-price/"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk Executive Compensation 2025 | NVO CEO Salary","url":"https://www.panabee.com/news/novo-nordisk-executive-compensation-2025"},{"title":"Meet Novo Nordisk's Executive Management team","url":"https://www.novonordisk.com/about/executive-management.html"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk A/S (NOVO B) Leadership & Management Team Analysis - Simply Wall St","url":"https://simplywall.st/stocks/dk/pharmaceuticals-biotech/cph-novo-b/novo-nordisk-shares/management"},{"title":"Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen","url":"https://www.novonordisk.com/about/executive-management/lars-fruergaard-jorgensen.html"},{"title":"Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen | ISPE | International Society for Pharmaceutical Engineering","url":"https://ispe.org/people/lars-fruergaard-jorgensen"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk Names New CEO; Makes Other Leadership Changes - DCAT Value Chain Insights","url":"https://www.dcatvci.org/top-industry-news/novo-nordisk-names-new-ceo-makes-other-leadership-changes/"},{"title":"NVO - Novo Nordisk AS ADR Executives | Morningstar","url":"https://www.morningstar.com/stocks/xnys/nvo/executive"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found regarding Novo Nordisk's CEO, CFO, management team, and compensation:\n\n## CEO Leadership Transition\n\nLars Fruergaard Jørgensen was the chief executive of Novo Nordisk between January 2017 and August 2025. Maziar Mike Doustdar has been appointed as president and chief executive officer, effective 7 August 2025.\n\n## CEO Compensation\n\nThe group's CEO, Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen, received a total remuneration package of DKK 57.1 million ($7.97 million) in 2024, of which 42% is not yet finally determined, and 45% is deferred. Upon departure on August 6, 2025, he received total exit payments and salary of DKK 123.6 million, including a DKK 42.9 million severance and DKK 22.0 million non-compete.\n\n## CFO Compensation\n\nNovo Nordisk's CFO, Karsten Munk Knudsen, reached 67% of his max return based on his individual performance.\n\n## Performance-Based Adjustments\n\nPart of the shortfall in Jørgensen's STIP came from a miss in the company's Purpose & Sustainability and Innovation & Therapeutic Focus subset, where the one area where the group fell short was diversity and inclusion.\n\nThe search results provide information from the 2024 and 2025 proxy materials regarding compensation details for executive leadership."],"durationSeconds":9.918701916999998}}
