{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014uwUTULUZYDVCBWyyUyGwQ","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Novo Nordisk competitors Eli Lilly AstraZeneca GLP-1 market share risks 2025 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Who's Winning the Intense Battle to Rule the White-Hot GLP-1 Drug Market? | The Motley Fool\",\"url\":\"https://www.fool.com/investing/2025/11/11/win-intense-battle-rule-glp-1-drug-lly-nvo-pfe/\"},{\"title\":\"GLP-1 Medications: A Market on the Rise\",\"url\":\"https://redbock.com/news/glp-1-medications-a-market-on-the-rise/\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk (Denmark) and Eli Lilly (US) are Leading Players in the GLP-1 Agonists Market\",\"url\":\"https://www.marketsandmarkets.com/ResearchInsight/glp-1-analogues-market.asp\"},{\"title\":\"Eli Lilly's GLP-1 growth is only getting started as Novo Nordisk braces for a decline in 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/04/eli-lilly-novo-nordisk-earnings-glp1-market.html\"},{\"title\":\"What is Competitive Landscape of Novo Nordisk Company? – MatrixBCG.com\",\"url\":\"https://matrixbcg.com/blogs/competitors/novonordisk\"},{\"title\":\"2 Major Stocks Want to Dominate the GLP-1 Market. Which One Looks Like the Leader Heading Into 2026? | The Motley Fool\",\"url\":\"https://www.fool.com/investing/2025/11/22/2-major-stocks-want-to-dominate-the-glp-1-market/\"},{\"title\":\"GLP-1 Receptor Agonist Market Size | Industry Report, 2033\",\"url\":\"https://www.grandviewresearch.com/industry-analysis/glp-1-receptor-agonist-market\"},{\"title\":\"What is Competitive Landscape of Novo Nordisk Company? – PortersFiveForce.com\",\"url\":\"https://portersfiveforce.com/blogs/competitors/novonordisk\"},{\"title\":\"The leading GLP-1 contenders in pharma’s race for an obesity pill | PharmaVoice\",\"url\":\"https://www.pharmavoice.com/news/glp-1-pharma-obesity-pill-drug-novo-viking-structure-lilly/808195/\"},{\"title\":\"3 ways the GLP-1 market has changed shape this year | PharmaVoice\",\"url\":\"https://www.pharmavoice.com/news/glp-1-market-changes-eli-lilly-novo-nordisk-earnings/757312/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's comprehensive information about Novo Nordisk's competitors, market share dynamics, and risks in the GLP-1 market for 2025-2026:\n\n## Market Share Overview\n\nAs of Q2 2025, Eli Lilly holds approximately 57% of the GLP-1 market, having overtaken Novo Nordisk earlier this year. Novo Nordisk's market share had declined to 49.3% as of August, down from 55.7% the previous year. This represents a significant shift in the competitive landscape.\n\n## Key Competitors\n\n**Eli Lilly** is the primary competitor. Eli Lilly's GLP-1 drug is now the world's best-selling drug. Eli Lilly leverages its dual agonist tirzepatide (Mounjaro, Zepbound), and is innovating with next-generation oral GLP-1 receptor agonists, such as orforglipron, offering enhanced patient accessibility and adherence by eliminating injection barriers.\n\nBeyond Eli Lilly, companies like GSK plc, AstraZeneca, Boehringer Ingelheim, and Pfizer are developing new GLP-1 drugs. Pfizer is looking to enter the fray of the intense GLP-1 competition.\n\n## Major Risks for Novo Nordisk in 2025-2026\n\n**Market Share Loss:** Novo Nordisk is struggling with declining market share. Novo is bracing for a sales decline in 2026.\n\n**Pricing Pressure:** Both companies struck Trump administration deals to slash obesity and diabetes drug costs, creating significant headwinds. Both companies struck a deal with the Trump administration to significantly cut prices for their anti-obesity drugs for Medicare and Medicaid patients, with Zepbound's price for these patients dropping from $1,000 to $299 for a month's supply.\n\n**Product Efficacy Competition:** Novo's Wegovy pill promotes comparable weight loss to its injectable counterpart of around 15%, while Lilly's pill appears to be slightly less effective than that based on separate study data.\n\n**Compounded Alternatives:** The U.S. market has seen a rise in compounded GLP-1 alternatives, which challenge Novo Nordisk's pricing power and market share.\n\n## Market Growth Outlook\n\nThe global GLP-1 market was valued at about $52 billion in 2024 and is expected to rise to $187 billion by 2032, for compound annual growth of almost 17%.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eafad868-0c85-44e0-a96c-5a256a92aae5","uuid":"23435e13-2b77-4cad-8cf8-c6129d4d8a30","timestamp":"2026-04-28T22:42:35.290Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"Novo Nordisk competitors Eli Lilly AstraZeneca GLP-1 market share risks 2025 2026","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_019QYbXJnJBK9P3bDcns447M","content":[{"title":"Who's Winning the Intense Battle to Rule the White-Hot GLP-1 Drug Market? | The Motley Fool","url":"https://www.fool.com/investing/2025/11/11/win-intense-battle-rule-glp-1-drug-lly-nvo-pfe/"},{"title":"GLP-1 Medications: A Market on the Rise","url":"https://redbock.com/news/glp-1-medications-a-market-on-the-rise/"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk (Denmark) and Eli Lilly (US) are Leading Players in the GLP-1 Agonists Market","url":"https://www.marketsandmarkets.com/ResearchInsight/glp-1-analogues-market.asp"},{"title":"Eli Lilly's GLP-1 growth is only getting started as Novo Nordisk braces for a decline in 2026","url":"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/04/eli-lilly-novo-nordisk-earnings-glp1-market.html"},{"title":"What is Competitive Landscape of Novo Nordisk Company? – MatrixBCG.com","url":"https://matrixbcg.com/blogs/competitors/novonordisk"},{"title":"2 Major Stocks Want to Dominate the GLP-1 Market. Which One Looks Like the Leader Heading Into 2026? | The Motley Fool","url":"https://www.fool.com/investing/2025/11/22/2-major-stocks-want-to-dominate-the-glp-1-market/"},{"title":"GLP-1 Receptor Agonist Market Size | Industry Report, 2033","url":"https://www.grandviewresearch.com/industry-analysis/glp-1-receptor-agonist-market"},{"title":"What is Competitive Landscape of Novo Nordisk Company? – PortersFiveForce.com","url":"https://portersfiveforce.com/blogs/competitors/novonordisk"},{"title":"The leading GLP-1 contenders in pharma’s race for an obesity pill | PharmaVoice","url":"https://www.pharmavoice.com/news/glp-1-pharma-obesity-pill-drug-novo-viking-structure-lilly/808195/"},{"title":"3 ways the GLP-1 market has changed shape this year | PharmaVoice","url":"https://www.pharmavoice.com/news/glp-1-market-changes-eli-lilly-novo-nordisk-earnings/757312/"}]},"Based on the search results, here's comprehensive information about Novo Nordisk's competitors, market share dynamics, and risks in the GLP-1 market for 2025-2026:\n\n## Market Share Overview\n\nAs of Q2 2025, Eli Lilly holds approximately 57% of the GLP-1 market, having overtaken Novo Nordisk earlier this year. Novo Nordisk's market share had declined to 49.3% as of August, down from 55.7% the previous year. This represents a significant shift in the competitive landscape.\n\n## Key Competitors\n\n**Eli Lilly** is the primary competitor. Eli Lilly's GLP-1 drug is now the world's best-selling drug. Eli Lilly leverages its dual agonist tirzepatide (Mounjaro, Zepbound), and is innovating with next-generation oral GLP-1 receptor agonists, such as orforglipron, offering enhanced patient accessibility and adherence by eliminating injection barriers.\n\nBeyond Eli Lilly, companies like GSK plc, AstraZeneca, Boehringer Ingelheim, and Pfizer are developing new GLP-1 drugs. Pfizer is looking to enter the fray of the intense GLP-1 competition.\n\n## Major Risks for Novo Nordisk in 2025-2026\n\n**Market Share Loss:** Novo Nordisk is struggling with declining market share. Novo is bracing for a sales decline in 2026.\n\n**Pricing Pressure:** Both companies struck Trump administration deals to slash obesity and diabetes drug costs, creating significant headwinds. Both companies struck a deal with the Trump administration to significantly cut prices for their anti-obesity drugs for Medicare and Medicaid patients, with Zepbound's price for these patients dropping from $1,000 to $299 for a month's supply.\n\n**Product Efficacy Competition:** Novo's Wegovy pill promotes comparable weight loss to its injectable counterpart of around 15%, while Lilly's pill appears to be slightly less effective than that based on separate study data.\n\n**Compounded Alternatives:** The U.S. market has seen a rise in compounded GLP-1 alternatives, which challenge Novo Nordisk's pricing power and market share.\n\n## Market Growth Outlook\n\nThe global GLP-1 market was valued at about $52 billion in 2024 and is expected to rise to $187 billion by 2032, for compound annual growth of almost 17%."],"durationSeconds":9.995498875000004}}
