{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AyDYBJaRztTPx2ismTbQVn","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Novo Nordisk Maziar Doustdar new CEO background profile August 2025\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Mike Doustdar, President and Chief Executive Officer (CEO)\",\"url\":\"https://www.novonordisk.com/about/executive-management/maziar-mike-doustdar.html\"},{\"title\":\"Maziar Mike Doustdar: Novo Nordisk's New CEO\",\"url\":\"https://quartr.com/insights/business-philosophy/maziar-mike-doustdar-novo-nordisks-new-ceo\"},{\"title\":\"Company announcement\",\"url\":\"https://www.novonordisk.com/content/nncorp/global/en/news-and-media/news-and-ir-materials/news-details.html?id=916408\"},{\"title\":\"Maziar Mike Doustdar - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maziar_Mike_Doustdar\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk Names Maziar Mike Doustdar as President and Chief Executive Officer | PharmExec\",\"url\":\"https://www.pharmexec.com/view/novo-nordisk-maziar-mike-doustdar-president-ceo\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk Appoints New President & CEO | Contract Pharma\",\"url\":\"https://www.contractpharma.com/breaking-news/novo-nordisk-appoints-new-president-ceo/\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk Names New CEO; Makes Other Leadership Changes - DCAT Value Chain Insights\",\"url\":\"https://www.dcatvci.org/top-industry-news/novo-nordisk-names-new-ceo-makes-other-leadership-changes/\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk appoints Maziar Mike Doustdar as president and CEO - PMLiVE\",\"url\":\"https://pmlive.com/pharma_appointments/novo-nordisk-appoints-maziar-mike-doustdar-as-president-and-ceo/\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk Appoints New CEO Mike Doustdar\",\"url\":\"https://www.pharmanow.live/latest-news/novo-nordisk-new-ceo-mike-doustdar-2025\"},{\"title\":\"Novo Nordisk Appoints Mike Doustdar as New CEO Amid Executive Reshuffle\",\"url\":\"https://medicaldialogues.in/news/industry/pharma/novo-nordisk-appoints-mike-doustdar-as-new-ceo-amid-executive-reshuffle-152721\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's a comprehensive profile of Maziar Mike Doustdar, Novo Nordisk's new CEO:\n\n## Appointment and Background\n\nMaziar Mike Doustdar is an Austrian–Iranian business executive who has served as the president and chief executive officer (CEO) of Novo Nordisk since 7 August 2025. Novo Nordisk announced Doustdar's appointment on 29 July 2025, succeeding Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen, effective 7 August 2025.\n\n## Personal Background\n\nDoustdar was born in August 1970 in Iran, is an Austrian national, and grew up in the United States. He earned a Bachelor of Arts in International Business from Webster University's Vienna campus (graduating in 1994) and later studied at Harvard Business School, focusing on Leadership & Strategy for Pharmaceutical and Biotech. He is fluent in English, Farsi, and German.\n\n## Career at Novo Nordisk\n\nDoustdar joined Novo Nordisk in 1992 as an office clerk in Vienna while still at university. In 2013 he was promoted to senior vice president of Novo Nordisk's International Operations, and in April 2015 he was promoted to executive vice president. By 2025, the geographical responsibility of International Operations under his tenure included all global commercial units, excluding the USA. Over the last decade, he more than doubled sales in Novo Nordisk's international markets, reaching approximately DKK 112 billion in 2024.\n\n## Recognition\n\nDoustdar was included on the 2026 Time 100 list of most influential people in health for his work at Novo Nordisk.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eafad868-0c85-44e0-a96c-5a256a92aae5","uuid":"ac132cbc-28f5-44cd-90dd-26f38e3a14b5","timestamp":"2026-04-28T22:43:29.313Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"Novo Nordisk Maziar Doustdar new CEO background profile August 2025","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01LVUF1VvjXPJDLTAoiT1kww","content":[{"title":"Mike Doustdar, President and Chief Executive Officer (CEO)","url":"https://www.novonordisk.com/about/executive-management/maziar-mike-doustdar.html"},{"title":"Maziar Mike Doustdar: Novo Nordisk's New CEO","url":"https://quartr.com/insights/business-philosophy/maziar-mike-doustdar-novo-nordisks-new-ceo"},{"title":"Company announcement","url":"https://www.novonordisk.com/content/nncorp/global/en/news-and-media/news-and-ir-materials/news-details.html?id=916408"},{"title":"Maziar Mike Doustdar - Wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maziar_Mike_Doustdar"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk Names Maziar Mike Doustdar as President and Chief Executive Officer | PharmExec","url":"https://www.pharmexec.com/view/novo-nordisk-maziar-mike-doustdar-president-ceo"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk Appoints New President & CEO | Contract Pharma","url":"https://www.contractpharma.com/breaking-news/novo-nordisk-appoints-new-president-ceo/"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk Names New CEO; Makes Other Leadership Changes - DCAT Value Chain Insights","url":"https://www.dcatvci.org/top-industry-news/novo-nordisk-names-new-ceo-makes-other-leadership-changes/"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk appoints Maziar Mike Doustdar as president and CEO - PMLiVE","url":"https://pmlive.com/pharma_appointments/novo-nordisk-appoints-maziar-mike-doustdar-as-president-and-ceo/"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk Appoints New CEO Mike Doustdar","url":"https://www.pharmanow.live/latest-news/novo-nordisk-new-ceo-mike-doustdar-2025"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk Appoints Mike Doustdar as New CEO Amid Executive Reshuffle","url":"https://medicaldialogues.in/news/industry/pharma/novo-nordisk-appoints-mike-doustdar-as-new-ceo-amid-executive-reshuffle-152721"}]},"Based on the search results, here's a comprehensive profile of Maziar Mike Doustdar, Novo Nordisk's new CEO:\n\n## Appointment and Background\n\nMaziar Mike Doustdar is an Austrian–Iranian business executive who has served as the president and chief executive officer (CEO) of Novo Nordisk since 7 August 2025. Novo Nordisk announced Doustdar's appointment on 29 July 2025, succeeding Lars Fruergaard Jørgensen, effective 7 August 2025.\n\n## Personal Background\n\nDoustdar was born in August 1970 in Iran, is an Austrian national, and grew up in the United States. He earned a Bachelor of Arts in International Business from Webster University's Vienna campus (graduating in 1994) and later studied at Harvard Business School, focusing on Leadership & Strategy for Pharmaceutical and Biotech. He is fluent in English, Farsi, and German.\n\n## Career at Novo Nordisk\n\nDoustdar joined Novo Nordisk in 1992 as an office clerk in Vienna while still at university. In 2013 he was promoted to senior vice president of Novo Nordisk's International Operations, and in April 2015 he was promoted to executive vice president. By 2025, the geographical responsibility of International Operations under his tenure included all global commercial units, excluding the USA. Over the last decade, he more than doubled sales in Novo Nordisk's international markets, reaching approximately DKK 112 billion in 2024.\n\n## Recognition\n\nDoustdar was included on the 2026 Time 100 list of most influential people in health for his work at Novo Nordisk."],"durationSeconds":6.661749167000002}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012WZ6Ft8dxuwsWkS2g5Dion","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I now have a solid foundation of data. Let me do a few more searches to fill the remaining gaps:\n\n1. NVO geographic revenue - North America percentage\n2. Analyst ratings with specific firm names and price targets\n3. Return on capital historical data\n4. NVO's Karsten Munk Knudsen (CFO) information\n5. Risk factors from the annual report\n\nLet me also compute some figures from what I have:\n- USD/DKK exchange rate for 2025: approximately 1 USD = 6.60 DKK (roughly)\n  - 2025 Revenue: DKK 309,064M / 6.60 = $46.8B\n  - 2024 Revenue: DKK 290,403M / 6.60 = $44.0B\n\nI'm noticing some discrepancies between the reported USD figures and my conversions—the 2024 number came in at $42.1B in one source but my calculation gives $44.0B. Rather than chase down the exchange rate variations, I'll stick with the DKK figures for consistency.\n\nNow I'm looking at the full revenue history in both currencies. The DKK numbers show strong growth through 2024 with a 25% increase, then a significant slowdown to 6.4% in 2025. Converting to USD at roughly 6.60 gives me the approximate dollar equivalents, though the exact rate varies slightly depending on the source. I can also see the revenue breakdown starting to come through, with diabetes care being a major segment.\n\nLooking at the segment details for 2025, diabetes care dominates at 67% of revenue with Ozempic as the clear driver at 41%, while obesity care is growing rapidly at 27% with Wegovy as the primary contributor. I'm trying to pin down Wegovy's full-year figure by working backward from the quarterly data—Q3 showed about DKK 20B, and the nine-month total was DKK 59.9B, which should help me estimate the complete year. the majority. Saxenda is declining as it's being replaced by Wegovy. Now I need to look at the geographic breakdown, particularly North America, since the US market is driving most of the obesity drug growth through insurance coverage and reimbursement decisions.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1026,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2097,"cache_read_input_tokens":52466,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2097},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eafad868-0c85-44e0-a96c-5a256a92aae5","uuid":"3983c41e-9448-4bed-b71c-8133efdfc5e7"}
