{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014TiKEbKuVzCmp1zBjWxiTu","type":"tool_result","content":"# Novo Nordisk 2025 Financial Summary\n\n## Regional Revenue Split\nThe document does not provide specific DKK millions for US vs. International Operations separately. However, it notes:\n- **US Operations**: Sales increased 3% in Danish kroner (8% at constant exchange rates)\n- **International Operations**: Sales increased 10% in Danish kroner (14% at constant exchange rates)\n\n## Product-Level Revenue\nNo specific revenue figures are disclosed for Wegovy or Saxenda individually. The report only provides combined metrics:\n- **Obesity and Diabetes care**: DKK 289.5 billion total\n- **Obesity care growth**: 26% in Danish kroner (31% at CER)\n- **GLP-1 diabetes sales**: 2% growth in Danish kroner (6% at CER)\n\n## FY2026 Guidance\nAdjusted sales growth is expected to be **-5% to -13% at constant exchange rates**, with reported Danish kroner growth approximately 3 percentage points lower. The outlook notes \"lower realised prices\" and impacts from the \"Most Favoured Nations\" agreement and \"patent expiry of the semaglutide molecule in certain IO markets.\"\n\n## Operating Profit Details\n- **2025 Operating Profit**: DKK 127.7 billion (down 1% as reported; up 6% at CER)\n- **Transformation costs**: Approximately DKK 8 billion reduced reported growth\n- **2026 Guidance**: Adjusted operating profit growth expected at **-5% to -13% at CER**\n\n## Semaglutide Patent/Pricing Pressure\nThe company explicitly identifies \"patent expiry of the semaglutide molecule in certain IO markets\" and \"lower realised prices\" as key 2026 headwinds, alongside competitive pressures."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eafad868-0c85-44e0-a96c-5a256a92aae5","uuid":"0bb3cbf3-075e-4830-9b6b-4d06de1b0ff0","timestamp":"2026-04-28T22:44:02.310Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":53286,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Novo Nordisk 2025 Financial Summary\n\n## Regional Revenue Split\nThe document does not provide specific DKK millions for US vs. International Operations separately. However, it notes:\n- **US Operations**: Sales increased 3% in Danish kroner (8% at constant exchange rates)\n- **International Operations**: Sales increased 10% in Danish kroner (14% at constant exchange rates)\n\n## Product-Level Revenue\nNo specific revenue figures are disclosed for Wegovy or Saxenda individually. The report only provides combined metrics:\n- **Obesity and Diabetes care**: DKK 289.5 billion total\n- **Obesity care growth**: 26% in Danish kroner (31% at CER)\n- **GLP-1 diabetes sales**: 2% growth in Danish kroner (6% at CER)\n\n## FY2026 Guidance\nAdjusted sales growth is expected to be **-5% to -13% at constant exchange rates**, with reported Danish kroner growth approximately 3 percentage points lower. The outlook notes \"lower realised prices\" and impacts from the \"Most Favoured Nations\" agreement and \"patent expiry of the semaglutide molecule in certain IO markets.\"\n\n## Operating Profit Details\n- **2025 Operating Profit**: DKK 127.7 billion (down 1% as reported; up 6% at CER)\n- **Transformation costs**: Approximately DKK 8 billion reduced reported growth\n- **2026 Guidance**: Adjusted operating profit growth expected at **-5% to -13% at CER**\n\n## Semaglutide Patent/Pricing Pressure\nThe company explicitly identifies \"patent expiry of the semaglutide molecule in certain IO markets\" and \"lower realised prices\" as key 2026 headwinds, alongside competitive pressures.","durationMs":6808,"url":"https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/2/3/3231383/0/en/Novo-Nordisk-s-sales-increased-by-6-in-Danish-kroner-and-by-10-at-constant-exchange-rates-to-DKK-309-1-billion-in-2025.html"}}
