{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016cmFrKwFENWk8ky8SayQQp","type":"tool_result","content":"# Novo Nordisk 2025 Financial Data Summary\n\n## Revenue Breakdown by Therapeutic Area\n\n**Total Sales: DKK 309,064 million (10% growth at CER)**\n\n### Obesity Care\n- **DKK 82,347 million** (26% growth in DKK; 31% at CER)\n- Driven by both US and International Operations\n- Global branded market share: 59.6%\n\n### Diabetes Care\n- **DKK 207,109 million** (unchanged in DKK; 4% growth at CER)\n- Primary driver: GLP-1-based products\n\n**GLP-1 Diabetes Products: DKK 152,202 million**\n- Ozempic®: DKK 127,089 million (10% growth at CER)\n- Rybelsus®: DKK 22,093 million (-2% at CER)\n- Victoza®: DKK 3,020 million (-43% at CER)\n\n**Insulin Sales: DKK 53,137 million** (-1% at CER)\n\n### Rare Disease\n- **DKK 19,608 million** (9% growth at CER)\n  - Rare endocrine disorders: DKK 5,959 million\n  - Rare blood disorders: DKK 11,955 million\n\n## Geographic Revenue Breakdown\n\n- **US Operations**: 3% growth (DKK); 8% at CER\n- **International Operations**: 10% growth (DKK); 14% at CER\n  - EUCAN: 16% at CER\n  - APAC: 25% at CER\n  - Emerging Markets: 8% at CER\n  - Region China: 5% at CER\n\n## Profitability\n\n- **Gross Margin**: 81.0% (down from 84.7% in 2024)\n- **Operating Profit**: DKK 127,658 million (-1% in DKK; 6% at CER)\n- **Net Profit**: DKK 102,434 million (1% growth)\n- **Diluted EPS**: DKK 23.03 (2% growth)\n- **Effective Tax Rate**: 21.5%\n\n## Cash Flow & Capital Allocation\n\n- **Free Cash Flow**: DKK 28.3 billion (vs. negative DKK 14.7 billion in 2024)\n- **Capital Expenditure (PP&E)**: DKK 60.1 billion\n- **Intangible Assets CapEx**: DKK 30.0 billion (reflecting Akero Therapeutics acquisition)\n\n## 2026 Guidance\n\n**Adjusted Sales Growth (CER)**: -5% to -13%\n\n**Adjusted Operating Profit Growth (CER)**: -5% to -13%\n\n### Key Modeling Considerations:\n- Financial items (net): \"Gain of around 2.3 bDKK\"\n- Effective tax rate: 21-23%\n- Capital expenditure: ~DKK 55 billion\n- Free cash flow: DKK 35-45 billion\n\n## Strategic Context\n\nThe decline reflects expected headwinds including the \"MFN agreement in the US,\" competitive pressures, and \"loss of exclusivity for the semaglutide molecule in certain markets.\" Offsetting factors include continued GLP-1 market expansion and Wegovy® oral formulation launch in January 2026."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2207cdf7-0767-4a59-9a1b-a30564847c67","uuid":"587096f5-90d6-4bac-a4e8-e77e8e50282b","timestamp":"2026-04-28T23:21:53.103Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":386579,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Novo Nordisk 2025 Financial Data Summary\n\n## Revenue Breakdown by Therapeutic Area\n\n**Total Sales: DKK 309,064 million (10% growth at CER)**\n\n### Obesity Care\n- **DKK 82,347 million** (26% growth in DKK; 31% at CER)\n- Driven by both US and International Operations\n- Global branded market share: 59.6%\n\n### Diabetes Care\n- **DKK 207,109 million** (unchanged in DKK; 4% growth at CER)\n- Primary driver: GLP-1-based products\n\n**GLP-1 Diabetes Products: DKK 152,202 million**\n- Ozempic®: DKK 127,089 million (10% growth at CER)\n- Rybelsus®: DKK 22,093 million (-2% at CER)\n- Victoza®: DKK 3,020 million (-43% at CER)\n\n**Insulin Sales: DKK 53,137 million** (-1% at CER)\n\n### Rare Disease\n- **DKK 19,608 million** (9% growth at CER)\n  - Rare endocrine disorders: DKK 5,959 million\n  - Rare blood disorders: DKK 11,955 million\n\n## Geographic Revenue Breakdown\n\n- **US Operations**: 3% growth (DKK); 8% at CER\n- **International Operations**: 10% growth (DKK); 14% at CER\n  - EUCAN: 16% at CER\n  - APAC: 25% at CER\n  - Emerging Markets: 8% at CER\n  - Region China: 5% at CER\n\n## Profitability\n\n- **Gross Margin**: 81.0% (down from 84.7% in 2024)\n- **Operating Profit**: DKK 127,658 million (-1% in DKK; 6% at CER)\n- **Net Profit**: DKK 102,434 million (1% growth)\n- **Diluted EPS**: DKK 23.03 (2% growth)\n- **Effective Tax Rate**: 21.5%\n\n## Cash Flow & Capital Allocation\n\n- **Free Cash Flow**: DKK 28.3 billion (vs. negative DKK 14.7 billion in 2024)\n- **Capital Expenditure (PP&E)**: DKK 60.1 billion\n- **Intangible Assets CapEx**: DKK 30.0 billion (reflecting Akero Therapeutics acquisition)\n\n## 2026 Guidance\n\n**Adjusted Sales Growth (CER)**: -5% to -13%\n\n**Adjusted Operating Profit Growth (CER)**: -5% to -13%\n\n### Key Modeling Considerations:\n- Financial items (net): \"Gain of around 2.3 bDKK\"\n- Effective tax rate: 21-23%\n- Capital expenditure: ~DKK 55 billion\n- Free cash flow: DKK 35-45 billion\n\n## Strategic Context\n\nThe decline reflects expected headwinds including the \"MFN agreement in the US,\" competitive pressures, and \"loss of exclusivity for the semaglutide molecule in certain markets.\" Offsetting factors include continued GLP-1 market expansion and Wegovy® oral formulation launch in January 2026.","durationMs":10212,"url":"https://annualreport.novonordisk.com/2025/strategic-aspirations/financial-performance.html"}}
