26\",\"url\":\"https://markets.financialcontent.com/wral/article/finterra-2026-2-27-the-valuation-reset-a-deep-dive-into-novo-nordisk-nvo-in-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Semaglutide (Ozempic) Market: Navigating The Patent Cliff And Strategic Implications\",\"url\":\"https://www.grandviewresearch.com/market-trends/semaglutide-market-navigating-patent-cliff-strategic-implications\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's a comprehensive overview of Novo Nordisk's key risks:\n\n## Patent Expiration Timeline\n\nNovo Nordisk's semaglutide patent in India expires on March 20, 2026, and in 2026, Novo Nordisk's patent on semaglutide will expire in several countries, including India and China. More specifically, its patent in China is set to expire in 2026. As the timeline progresses into 2026-2027, the revenue loss is expected to be more pronounced, with this period marking the onset of localized patent expirations in key emerging markets such as China, Brazil, India, and Canada, which are projected to result in a 5-8% share loss.\n\n## GLP-1 Competition Challenges\n\nCagriSema failed to achieve non-inferior weight loss versus Eli Lilly's tirzepatide in the pivotal REDEFINE-4 study, undermining NVO's obesity drug pipeline momentum. NVO faces a -5% to -13% sales growth outlook for 2026, pressured by generic semaglutide entry in some markets and a thin late-stage pipeline.\n\n## Pricing Pressure and Market Impact\n\nIndian pharma giants like Zydus, Dr. Reddy's, and Cipla are poised to launch over 50 branded generics, slashing prices to 30-50% of Novo's current Rs 8,800-11,175 monthly cost. Goldman Sachs analysts project potential price reductions of around 25% for semaglutide in China.\n\n## Patent Timeline Details\n\nInterestingly, patents filed as an international application on March 20, 2006 should technically expire on March 20, 2026, while the '122 patent expires on March 20, 2026, its related patent, '343, will expire over five years later on December 5, 2031.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2207cdf7-0767-4a59-9a1b-a30564847c67","uuid":"21535e4d-0166-4f0b-beb8-2c0ddef3d867","timestamp":"2026-04-28T23:22:13.673Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"Novo Nordisk NVO risks GLP-1 competition CagriSema Ozempic patent expiry 2025 2026","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01WmeS6VqBjrJYjY7hPgii68","content":[{"title":"The Battle for Billions: Understanding the Ozempic Patent ...","url":"https://journals.library.columbia.edu/index.php/stlr/blog/view/653"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk: Downgrading To 'Sell' As GLP-1 Pipeline Faces Many Risks (NYSE:NVO) | Seeking Alpha","url":"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4888549-novo-nordisk-downgrading-to-sell-as-glp-1-pipeline-faces-many-risks"},{"title":"The Heavy Price of GLP-1 Drugs: How Financialization Drives Pharmaceutical Patent Abuse and Health Inequities for GLP-1 Therapies","url":"https://www.i-mak.org/glp-1/"},{"title":"March 20 Patent Expiry Set to Trigger Brutal GLP-1 Price War in India—Novo Nordisk’s Pricing Power Under Direct Threat","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/march-20-patent-expiry-set-trigger-brutal-glp-1-price-war-india-novo-nordisk-pricing-power-direct-threat-2603/"},{"title":"Looming GLP-1 drug patent expirations draw generics firms","url":"https://cen.acs.org/pharmaceuticals/Looming-GLP-1-drug-patent/103/web/2025/12"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk: Is The GLP‑1 Golden Age Already Behind It? (NYSE:NVO) | Seeking Alpha","url":"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4892731-novo-nordisk-is-the-glp1-golden-age-already-behind-it"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk CFO on 'silver bullet' to address GLP ...","url":"https://fortune.com/2025/11/06/novo-nordisk-pantent-innovation-market-leader-cfo-exclusive/"},{"title":"Novo Nordisk Gets Discounted as Investors Look Past the Next Phase of GLP-1 Growth | Investing.com","url":"https://www.investing.com/analysis/novo-nordisk-gets-discounted-as-investors-look-pa